title: Missile haul intercepted by Royal Navy 'proves Iran is breaking UN resolutions'
description: A basic mistake by the Iranian military has helped prove it is breaching UN Security Council resolutions on drones and missiles, says the UK.

title: China has high-altitude balloon programme linked to army, White House says
description: The White House has determined that China has a "high-altitude balloon programme" for intelligence gathering.

title: Bereaved Turkish woman keeps warm across from home-turned-tomb where loved ones are trapped
description: Fatima Figen's whole world has gone.

title: Angry choreographer 'smears faeces on critic's face' after bad review
description: A choreographer has been suspended after reportedly smearing dog faeces on the face of a critic following a bad review.

title: Poor treatment of Liverpool fans 'almost led to disaster' says review of Champions League final chaos
description: A UEFA-commissioned review into the poor treatment of Liverpool fans outside the 2022 Champions League final is set to find the failings "almost led to a disaster" after faults by European football's governing body and the lack of a venue risk assessment by French authorities, Sky News can reveal.

title: Czech Republic footballer Jakub Jankto comes out as gay
description: Czech Republic midfielder Jakub Jankto has become one of the most high-profile male footballers to come out as gay.

title: British embassy guard was paid 'substantial amounts of cash' to spy for Russians
description: A security guard at the British embassy in Berlin received "substantial amounts of cash" from the Russians in return for "highly sensitive" secrets before he was caught in an undercover sting operation, a court has heard.

title: Syrian man who took refuge in Turkey searches for his lost loved ones under the rubble
description: When the Kenno family left Azaz, Syria a decade ago, fleeing the country's civil war, they chose to seek refuge in Kahramanmaras. A picturesque city sprawled along the Binboga mountain range.

title: China claims US balloons flew over its airspace 'more than 10 times over the past year'
description: China has claimed US high-altitude balloons have flown over its airspace more than 10 times over the past year.

title: Senior MPs attack government for meeting 'criminal' Chinese governor in London
description: Senior MPs from both the UK's main parties have attacked the government for allowing the governor of Xinjiang to come to the country, despite the persecution of Uyghur Muslims in his province.

title: Chinese ship used laser against coast guard vessel, Philippines says
description: The Philippines has accused a Chinese coast guard ship of hitting a Philippine coast guard vessel with a military-grade laser and temporarily blinding some of its crew in the disputed South China Sea.

title: Dubai's flying taxis could be launched as early as 2026
description: Flying taxis could be with us sooner than you think as Dubai hopes to launch its "aerial ridesharing" service by 2026.

title: EU economy projected to avoid recession
description: A more positive picture of the EU economy has been predicted: it is to avoid recession with lower inflation and higher growth than had been forecast.

title: Kansas City Chiefs fight back to narrowly beat Philadelphia Eagles in classic Super Bowl
description: The Kansas City Chiefs fought back to beat the Philadelphia Eagles in a classic Super Bowl that will be remembered as one of the greatest of all time.

title: Timeline of unidentified objects shot down after entering US airspace
description: US fighter jets have now shot down four flying objects in fewer than 10 days.

title: Mars attacks: Factory fined after staff hurt in chocolate accident
description: A factory which makes M&Ms and Mars bars has been fined more than $14,500 (£12,000) after an accident in which two workers fell into a vat of chocolate.

title: 'Possible' that 'hostile' China has sent spy balloons over UK
description: A minister has claimed it is "possible" Chinese spy balloons have already flown over the UK, as the government launches a security review into the threat.

title: US on heightened state of alert over flying objects - and it hasn't ruled out extra-terrestrials
description: In US political speak, they're fond of the phrase "an abundance of caution".
